        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 6:59AM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 658 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Scott, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Scott, Richards, Metz, Stotesbury, Hammond, and Horton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
